From the Land Life series project

Smoke-Fire Sequence

Ghirdoveni 2015

A study of the very short and volatile manifest nature of smoke and plasma fire sparked by the direct action and awareness of the artist, and sustained by the presence of the universal field Conscience and Earth natural energy. The field of mind together with the magnetic field of Earth determine the shape and dynamics of smoke and fire.

From the Land Life project series

Land Life

Editions: 2013, 2014, 2015, 2016, 2017, 2018

The ongoing project series is a manifesto of building physical structures to reconstruct natural cosmogony mindset, and raise consciousness against egocentric, artificial and eccentric use of human inhabited land.

The medium is local available materials. I look into a few critical characteristics of the object, like relative scale and distance to the surrounding elements, easy path and flow of energy currents, color, light, material harmony and contrast, etc…

Gentry Birds Illustration Project

Gentry Ball Clock Bird

A study of various mid century inspired shapes translated into a collection of museum quality art prints with lavish sensations of vibrant hues and tones of colour. Originals painted in gouache and watercolor. The project is a collaboration with ElenaBerloOnceUponaPaper company.

Untitled Perishable Lightning Rod

Genu - 2016

Ghirdoveni Art Installation, corrugated kraft paper rolled, wood, metal rod

Waiting for the strike, a ludic exercise of exorcising my mom’s fear of storm and lightnings. I imagine here the mix of fear and excitement. Fear of visceral structural soundness against the joy and excitement of natural magic. Thus, I call this mixed feeling “Untitled Perishable Lightning Rod”, this being one of my artistic studies about Space-Time-Conscience relations and Emotional States of Matter and Mind in the context of Life and Magic.
